  "doc_id": "747",
  "text": "The median-effect principle has been employed to analyze the dose-response data in enzymatic, cellular, and animal studies. A few studies have used this approach to study the antimicrobial effects, such as the ones of using the median-effect equation to investigate the antiviral synergistic effect against human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) and influenza virus A (AsinMilan et al., 2014; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Most studies used the CompuSyn software to generate the medianeffect plot [CITATION_3] . However, this software does not consider the shape of dose-response. Hence, it cannot overcome some of the possible mathematical errors in combinational studies.",
